.TH OPEN-MAINFRAME-COMPILE 1 "February 2026" "OpenMainframe 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
open-mainframe-compile \- compile COBOL source files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B open-mainframe compile
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIFILE\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Compile a COBOL source file to native code using the LLVM backend.
The compiler supports both fixed-format (columns 1-72) and free-format
COBOL source.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIFILE\fR
Output file path. Defaults to input filename without extension.
.TP
.BR \-O ", " \-\-optimize " " \fILEVEL\fR
Optimization level (0-3). Default: 0.
.RS
.TP
.B 0
No optimization (fastest compile).
.TP
.B 1
Basic optimizations.
.TP
.B 2
Standard optimizations.
.TP
.B 3
Aggressive optimizations.
.RE
.TP
.BR \-\-emit\-asm
Emit assembly instead of object file.
.TP
.BR \-\-emit\-llvm
Emit LLVM IR instead of object file.
.TP
.BR \-I ", " \-\-include " " \fIDIR\fR
Additional copybook search paths. Can be specified multiple times.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Basic compilation:
.B open-mainframe compile program.cbl
.TP
Compile with output name:
.B open-mainframe compile program.cbl -o myprogram
.TP
Compile with optimization:
.B open-mainframe compile program.cbl -O2
.TP
Emit LLVM IR for debugging:
.B open-mainframe compile program.cbl --emit-llvm
.TP
Include copybook paths:
.B open-mainframe compile program.cbl -I /copy1 -I /copy2
